title: Biden hails freed U.S. hostages as family awaits reunion
description: Uri Raanan said he hopes to be reunited soon with daughter Natalie, 17, who was freed by Hamas militants after 13 days in captivity.

title: In Gaza war, Qatar revisits role as regional mediator
description: Small but influential, Qatar again flexes its role as a regional mediator.

title: Pakistan’s ex-premier returns from self-exile to country in turmoil
description: Sharif appeared poised to run for a fourth term as the country’s economy is in freefall and his main political rival, Imran Khan, in prison.

description: The families of Israelis held by Hamas try to make sense of the release of the surprise two American captives.

description: World leaders and diplomats attempted to build momentum for sustained humanitarian relief during a summit in Cairo.

title: Tammy strikes Lesser Antilles while Norma lashes Cabo San Lucas
description: The dual Atlantic and Pacific hurricanes show the season is still not over.

title: In photos: Humanitarian aid arrives in Gaza as Rafah crossing reopens
description: Trucks carrying food and medical supplies entered the Gaza Strip through the border crossing with Egypt for the first time since the start of Israel’s war with Hamas.

description: Islamic schools are concerned about threats, too. Administrators worry about how to pay for their security needs.

title: McDonald’s Mideast franchises offer side of politics with their burgers
description: As Israel’s war in Gaza spreads anger and anxiety across the Middle East, one of America’s most famous brands has found itself in the thick of it: McDonald’s.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: Humanitarian aid expected to move into Gaza this weekend
description: Trucks carrying urgent relief supplies remained stuck at the Egypt border as Gaza’s humanitarian crisis worsens. Hamas freed two American hostages taken in the Oct. 7 attack.

title: U.S. effort to free Gaza hostages accelerates as ground war looms
description: The release of Judith and Natalie Raanan has fueled hope that other Americans held hostage in Gaza may also be freed, but negotiators face numerous challenges.

title: Hundreds of Americans trapped in Gaza with ‘no place safe for us to go’
description: At least 400 Americans are trapped in Gaza as Israel mounts a siege of the enclave, cutting off supplies of food and water, amid a relentless aerial bombardment.
